## 5. Technical architecture

```
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ              UI Layer (Flutter)          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  Splash вҶ’ Login/Register вҶ’ Dashboard    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  Budget | Guests | Schedule | Settings   в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
                  в”Ӯ
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ           Services Layer                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  AuthService | WeddingRepository         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  FirestoreService | LocalWeddingStore    в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
          в”Ӯ               в”Ӯ
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
   в”Ӯ Local Store в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Firebase  в”Ӯ
   в”Ӯ SharedPrefs в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Auth + DB  в”Ӯ
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
```

**Pattern:** Repository pattern вҖ” `WeddingRepository` abstracts the data source (local or cloud).

---

## 6. Local storage and data retrieval

### 6.1 Embedded data (instructor demo mode)

File `mock_data.dart` вҖ” sample data for Siti & Ahmad to test without an account:
- 8 budget categories, 8 guests, 6 events, 7 vendors

### 6.2 Persistent storage (SharedPreferences)

Each registered user gets a private workspace:
- Registration вҶ’ `WeddingDataFactory.createNew()` вҶ’ JSON save
- Login вҶ’ `loadForUser()` вҶ’ personal data displayed

### 6.3 Retrieval example

```dart
// Simplified example
final profile = await WeddingRepository.instance.loadForUser(userId);
WeddingSession.activate(profile);
// Screens read MockData which points to WeddingSession
```

---

## 7. Networking and API consumption

### 7.1 Client-server architecture

```
[Flutter App]  вҶҗвҶ’  [Firebase Auth API]     (authentication)
[Flutter App]  вҶҗвҶ’  [Cloud Firestore API]   (wedding data)
```

### 7.2 Firestore collections

```
users/{userId}          вҶ’ email, name, role, weddingId
weddings/{weddingId}    вҶ’ brideName, groomName, weddingDate, budget...
weddings/{id}/guests/   вҶ’ guest list
```

### 7.3 Asynchronous processing

All network operations use `async/await`:
- `signIn()`, `register()`, `createWeddingProfile()`, `loadForUser()`

---

## 8. Error handling

```dart
// AuthResult pattern used across the app
final result = await authService.signIn(email: email, password: password);
if (result.isSuccess) {
  context.go('/home');
} else {
  setState(() => _error = result.error);  // Display to user
}
```

**Principles:**
- Client-side validation before API calls
- Catch `FirebaseAuthException` with readable messages
- Graceful fallback when Firebase is unavailable (demo mode)

